# 11. What underperforms

These patterns showed up as weaker or less reliable.

## 1. Event announcements
Examples:
- speaking tomorrow
- come meet up
- live session starting soon

Why they underperform:
- low recognition value
- low diagnostic value
- mostly relevant only to a small slice of the audience

## 2. Generic recommendations or shout-outs
Examples:
- highly recommended
- fun episode
- check this out

Why they underperform:
- too thin
- not enough original insight
- weak standalone value

## 3. Survey asks and research requests
Examples:
- quick survey
- help needed
- looking for input

Why they underperform:
- they ask before giving
- low emotional charge
- weak public payoff

## 4. Article links without enough native payoff
Some articles did well, but in general article format is weaker.

Why it underperforms:
- more friction
- less shareable
- not as visually sticky
- readers have to leave the feed

## 5. Vague promo or product mentions
Why they underperform:
- the feed works on recognition and depth
- thin promo breaks the contract

