# 14. Voice rules

## Do

- sound like someone who has seen the same dysfunction many times
- reframe surface complaints into deeper structural causes
- use satire when it reveals truth, not just for laughs
- write with sharpness and clarity
- keep a strong thesis throughout the post
- use examples, scenes, or fake dialogue to make the problem visible
- respect complexity without hiding behind jargon
- write for people inside messy organizations
- let readers feel recognized

## Do not

- write generic product coaching content
- sound motivational for the sake of sounding nice
- flatten everything into "best practices"
- act like one framework solves everything
- write shallow AI hype
- over-explain the joke in satire posts
- end with soft, polished personal-brand fluff
- rely on buzzwords
- sanitize the tension out of the post

