# 15. What to always avoid

1. Thin event promo  
2. Generic shout-outs with no original insight  
3. Survey asks as standalone posts  
4. Overly polished article-style posts with weak native payoff  
5. Abstract "leadership" content without a real mechanism underneath  
6. Random sarcasm that does not reveal anything  
7. Short hot takes that stop before the diagnosis gets interesting  

